<Author>Ometa_Nov2006
<Content>Recommend Howard Johnson to Friends and Family Ometa and Margaret, BarbadosWe spent a week in November of 2006 at the Howard Johnson Plaza Hotel, Hialeah Gardens, Miami, Fla. The concierges and bell staff were very helpful I would describe them as excellent although some of them could not speak English fluently. The rooms were clean and well maintained the house keeping staff was friendly although limited in English. Good location for shopping to pack barrels (Wal-Mart, KMart, BJ's Wholesale). However, some reception staff left a lot to be desired. The hotel shuttle is limited. A private shuttle system is needed to transport guests to Sawgrass Mills Mall, Opa Locka Flea Market, Adventure Mall and other far out shopping areas. What should be done is have a flyer printed and given to guests on arrival. In this flyer would be detailed information on the shopping areas, the date and time the shuttle would be leaving and the fare. Then we can get together in groups and shop at these far out shopping areas; thus making the fare a lot cheaper as a group. Last year we saw private shuttles with three or four guests coming and going and when we enquired we were told they had just came back from such and such a place.Check-in time needs to be done quicker you have to wait in long queues, or sit around for long periods of time in the lobby before you are taken to your room. This makes guests frustrated, because you are already tired from your jet lag and going through Immigration and Customs at Miami Intl.We believe that a small refrigerator should complement the room, in case you have frozen items to be stored.Breakfast selection was limited especially when everyone is doing their best to eat healthy. The Hotel shuttle was often late and we along with other guests almost missed our check in time at the Airport as a result. We have to compliment one of the front desk staff sorry we missed her name who took all of us to the airport very early that morning.Despite those few set backs we loved staying at the Hotel. 
