<Author>Bkconcept
<Content>Fool me Once Shame on you.. Fool me twice Shame on Me Let me start off this review by telling you that we went to this hotel back in 2005 and found it to be a hidden jewel in Miami, so when we were back in the area it was only natural to choose this hotel again. Boy were we mistaken!!The hotel itself hasn't changed. The hotel seemed clean and the rooms were your standard rooms. We booked the three rooms for February 19th. Upon arriving to the hotel we were greeted by a nice woman named Flor. She checked us in quickly and we made our way to our rooms. Two of the rooms were fine except the third room had the problem of the room's keys not working. We headed downstairs to see if they could fix the keys and was greeted by a woman who told us to wait until she was done cleaning off the counter before helping us. Finally after fixing the keys, or so we thought, she went back to cleaning. We went upstairs and the first key we tried didn't work, the second key opened the door to find that the room was already occupied. Thank goodness we are honest people because who knows what some people would have done in that situation. We headed back downstairs again, were the same woman who just handed us the keys looked at us like we were just checking in and not just down there with a problem. After telling her what we found she proceeded to give us another room, without apologizing nor finding out why she gave us a room that was already occupied. And to make matters worse one of the new key cards didn't work. This room was fine for the night. Let me repeat for the NIGHT. The next day we checked out and spent the day in Miami. About three hours before we were to head to the airport to fly home we received a call that our flight was canceled and would have to fly out the next morning. The cheapest rates in town, most likely because of the poor service, was the Howard Johnson. We called them to book two rooms for one more night and requested adjoining rooms. We went back to the hotel and waited 30 minutes to check in. When we checked in the lady at the front desk said that the hotel didn't have adjoining rooms, which was a lie because we were in a room with doors the connected to the next room just the night before. Not wanting to deal with their ignorance we went upstairs with our children ages 6 and 8, who were starving, to drop off our luggage and head out to eat. We opened one room and everything was fine. But low and behold when we entered into the second room the room was already occupied. We went downstairs furious and the woman said that the previous person staying in the room had checked out and that hotel cannot remove any possessions from the room until the owner comes to claim the items. Playing the devil's advocate I asked, You mean if they never come back to the room you will never have the room available? She looked at me as if she never thought of it that way and like a robot repeated. We cannot remove any items for the room. However, they can give a key to any body's room to rummage through their possessions if they choose. Anyway we asked her because their are not adjoining rooms in the hotel would we fit in the Penthouse. She said she has never been in the penthouse and doesn't know. We went upstairs and just a note. DON'T EVER BOOK THE PENTHOUSE. The only difference from the other rooms was they have a mini frig and a microwave. We went back downstairs and waiting 45 minutes before speaking to the woman again this time requesting a manager. We spoke with Danielle Torres, who just got done kissing some corporate woman's [--] because they messed up her room. She was so apologetic but when she went to help us she looked at us as if we were nothing. She reviewed the house keeping schedule and said that the room was clear when they checked it, as if we were lying about the room being occupied. She then proceeded to say that her staff was ignorant and not capable of doing their job. She gave us another room on the same floor and she said that was all she could do. After complaining she asked what we wanted from her. I told her that after all the aggravation the least she could do was discount our room. She said the room was already discounted with AAA and we already got a good rate $104.70 (with tax), but to show she was sorry she would discount our rooms by $10 each. At the end of my rope and knowing that the children were upstairs hungry I took the new keys and went upstairs. One of the couples we were with went into the new room and one member took a shower where he found a cockroach wandering around the bathroom. The next morning we checked out to find that Danielle never took off the $10 discount the rooms. We didn't notice until later but we only got the discount on one of the rooms not both as promised.Here is the real kicker. When we got home we found that we were billed for five nights on the first nights stay where we only had three rooms. We called the incompetent hotel and got no results so we had to call corporate to look into the matter. This hotel is not worth the price, nor the frustration unless you wanted to be treated like the lonely cockroach in the bathroom!! 
