<Author>CelticLover
<Content>DON'T MAKE THE MISTAKE OF BOOKING THIS HOTEL Hotel Location and AmenitiesThe hotel is located right next to a freeway and therefore all rooms suffer quite badly from heavy traffic noise that goes on all night. The windows are inadequate to prevent this noise permeating the rooms. Amenities - Pool, adequate, but nothing to write home about. Restaurant, functioning on restricted hours with no room service after 10pm. If you're flight gets in after 9 and you don't have a car, your only option is to order a Domino's pizza.....really, I'm not kidding. Not even milk for tea is provided in the rooms, and if you ask, they just say no (that is, if the person you deal with speaks English, which most of them do, in Pidgeon fashion).Lobby - smells of dampness. Internet services provided at a charge. Carpet in the lobby and the corridors was so thin, you could feel the ridges in the concrete directly underneath. Rooms, clean but basic. Again, thing carpet. Again, the smell of dampness was prevalent. Poor quality drapes that don't close (presumably to save in costs on fabric?) but just hang at the side of the window. Television, microwave. Bathroom spotless. Bed reasonably comfortable. Staff. Unhelpful, often with a very basic mastery of English which makes communication difficult. Even when communication could be achieved, their attitude was extremely unhelpful. Having stayed here, I would not do so again. I'd rather pay the extra to stay elsewhere. Book only if you are blind, deaf, don't mind not eating or having even the most basic creature comforts and you actually enjoy being given bad service. All in all, not good value for money. 
